查看change的分布状况

# change的期望和标准差

m <- mean(bd$change);
s <- sd(bd$change);

m;
## [1] 0.0005169786
s;
## [1] 0.01885391
# 在构造一条N(m, s)的正态曲线，看两者的相合情况

norm_df <- data.frame(change = rnorm(length(bd$date), mean = m, sd = s));

# 绘图

ggplot(bd, aes(change)) +
  geom_density() +
  geom_density(data = norm_df, color = 'red');

检验change是否符合正态分布

# 由于样本数较多，故使用ks检验

ks.test(bd$change, 'pnorm', m, s);
## Warning in ks.test(bd$change, "pnorm", m, s): ties should not be present
## for the Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
## 
##  One-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
## 
## data:  bd$change
## D = 0.095899, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: two-sided
# 密度分布图和ks检验都否定零假设，change 不符合正态分布

时间序列分析

offset <- 0;

prc <- ts(bd$price[(length(bd$date)-100-offset) : (length(bd$date)-offset)]);

fprc <- HoltWinters(prc, gamma = F);

plot(fprc)

fprc
## Holt-Winters exponential smoothing with trend and without seasonal component.
## 
## Call:
## HoltWinters(x = prc, gamma = F)
## 
## Smoothing parameters:
##  alpha: 1
##  beta : 0.1992487
##  gamma: FALSE
## 
## Coefficients:
##          [,1]
## a 2695.609000
## b   -6.597701
# 使用 forcast 包

if(!require('forecast')){
  install.packages('forecast');
  library('forecast');
}
## Loading required package: forecast
ffprc <- forecast.HoltWinters(fprc, h=10)

plot.forecast(ffprc)
